Add extra features and customization to your script

Usage:
  bashly add [--source NAME] LIBRARY [ARGS...] [--force --quiet]
  bashly add [--source NAME] --list
  bashly add (-h|--help)

Options:
  -s --source NAME
    Specify a different libraries source. NAME can be:
    
    * Path to a local libraries directory
    * GitHub (HTTPS) repository:  github:user/repo[//path@ref]
    * GitHub (SSH) repository:    github-ssh:user/repo[//path@ref]
    * Remote git repository:      git:repo-url.git[//path@ref]

  -f --force
    Overwrite existing files

  -l --list
    Show available libraries

  -q --quiet
    Do not show post-install messages

  -h --help
    Show this help
